``` r
# load the data
cds <- readRDS(file = "../output/trajectory_cds.rds")
seurat.obj.filtered <- LoadSeuratRds(file = "../output/trajectory_seurat_filt.rds")
```

This chunk below visualizes the cells in the cds object, coloring them
based on their partition assignments. Partitions represent clusters of
cells identified during trajectory analysis, and this plot helps assess
the overall clustering.

``` r
# plot the cells according to their partition
plot_cells(cds, color_cells_by="partition")
```

![](differential_marker_files/figure-gfm/unnamed-chunk-2-1.png)<!-- -->

This code below identifies genes with significant expression changes
across partitions or `pseudotime` using the k-nearest neighbor graph.
The graph_test function performs statistical tests to detect genes
associated with the trajectory or partitions.

``` r
# find the neighbot graphs for further analysis
pr_graph_test_res <- graph_test(cds, neighbor_graph="knn", cores=8)
```

``` r
pr_deg_ids <- row.names(subset(pr_graph_test_res, q_value < 0.05))
```

This code below identifies gene modules based on their co-expression
patterns among the significant genes (pr_deg_ids). Each module groups
genes with similar expression dynamics, aiding in understanding the
regulatory networks.

``` r
# find the gene modules
gene_module_df <- find_gene_modules(cds[pr_deg_ids,], resolution=1e-2)
```

This code below creates a cell_group_df to link each cell to its
partition. It then aggregates gene expression across partitions for each
identified gene module. The resulting matrix (agg_mat) contains the
average expression values of each module across partitions.

The heatmap of the aggregated gene expression (`agg_mat`) is drawn to
visualize how modules are expressed across partitions. Rows represent
gene modules, and columns represent partitions, with clustering applied
to group similar modules and partitions.

``` r
# create a cell group dataframe
cell_group_df <- tibble::tibble(cell=row.names(colData(cds)), 
                                cell_group=partitions(cds)[colnames(cds)])

# aggregate gene expression based one the cell type
agg_mat <- aggregate_gene_expression(cds, gene_module_df, cell_group_df)
row.names(agg_mat) <- stringr::str_c("Module ", row.names(agg_mat))
colnames(agg_mat) <- stringr::str_c("Partition ", colnames(agg_mat))

# draw the heatmap
pheatmap::pheatmap(agg_mat, cluster_rows=TRUE, cluster_cols=TRUE,
                   scale="column", clustering_method="ward.D2",
                   fontsize=6)
```
